Project Python Foundations: FoodHub Data Analysis¶

Marks: 60

Context¶

The number of restaurants in New York is increasing day by day. Lots of students and busy professionals rely on those restaurants due to their hectic lifestyles. Online food delivery service is a great option for them. It provides them with good food from their favorite restaurants. A food aggregator company FoodHub offers access to multiple restaurants through a single smartphone app.

The app allows the restaurants to receive a direct online order from a customer. The app assigns a delivery person from the company to pick up the order after it is confirmed by the restaurant. The delivery person then uses the map to reach the restaurant and waits for the food package. Once the food package is handed over to the delivery person, he/she confirms the pick-up in the app and travels to the customer's location to deliver the food. The delivery person confirms the drop-off in the app after delivering the food package to the customer. The customer can rate the order in the app. The food aggregator earns money by collecting a fixed margin of the delivery order from the restaurants.

Objective¶

The food aggregator company has stored the data of the different orders made by the registered customers in their online portal. They want to analyze the data to get a fair idea about the demand of different restaurants which will help them in enhancing their customer experience. Suppose you are hired as a Data Scientist in this company and the Data Science team has shared some of the key questions that need to be answered. Perform the data analysis to find answers to these questions that will help the company to improve the business.

Data Description¶

The data contains the different data related to a food order. The detailed data dictionary is given below.

Data Dictionary¶

  • order_id: Unique ID of the order
  • customer_id: ID of the customer who ordered the food
  • restaurant_name: Name of the restaurant
  • cuisine_type: Cuisine ordered by the customer
  • cost: Cost of the order
  • day_of_the_week: Indicates whether the order is placed on a weekday or weekend (The weekday is from Monday to Friday and the weekend is Saturday and Sunday)
  • rating: Rating given by the customer out of 5
  • food_preparation_time: Time (in minutes) taken by the restaurant to prepare the food. This is calculated by taking the difference between the timestamps of the restaurant's order confirmation and the delivery person's pick-up confirmation.
  • delivery_time: Time (in minutes) taken by the delivery person to deliver the food package. This is calculated by taking the difference between the timestamps of the delivery person's pick-up confirmation and drop-off information

Question 13: The company wants to provide a promotional offer in the advertisement of the restaurants. The condition to get the offer is that the restaurants must have a rating count of more than 50 and the average rating should be greater than 4. Find the restaurants fulfilling the criteria to get the promotional offer. [3 marks]¶

In [40]:
# get all rated records except not given.
df_rated = df[df['rating'] != 'Not given'].copy()
# converted rating col to int
df_rated['rating'] = df_rated['rating'].astype(int)
# get restaurant list with their rated orders count
rating_counts = df_rated['restaurant_name'].value_counts()
# create data frame.
df_rating_count = pd.DataFrame({'restaurant_name': rating_counts.index, 'rating_count': rating_counts.values})

Question 14: The company charges the restaurant 25% on the orders having cost greater than 20 dollars and 15% on the orders having cost greater than 5 dollars. Find the net revenue generated by the company across all orders. [3 marks]¶

In [43]:
# lambda function to calculate revenue based on order cost
compute_revenue = lambda x: x * 0.25 if x > 20 else (x * 0.15 if x > 5 else 0)
# set the computed revenue amount to new col revenue
df['Revenue'] = df['cost_of_the_order'].apply(compute_revenue)
# Get total revenue from revenue col
total_revenue = df['Revenue'].sum()
print('The net revenue is approximately', round(total_revenue, 2), 'dollars')

The net revenue is approximately 6166.3 dollars

Observations:¶

The net revenue is approximately 6166.3 dollars

Question 15: The company wants to analyze the total time required to deliver the food. What percentage of orders take more than 60 minutes to get delivered from the time the order is placed? (The food has to be prepared and then delivered.) [2 marks]¶

In [44]:
# calculate total time by adding food preparation and delivery time and assign to new col total time.
df['total_time'] = df[['food_preparation_time', 'delivery_time']].sum(axis=1)
# calculate percentage of orders which take more than 60 minutes to get delivered from the time the order is placed
percentage_over_60_minutes = np.mean(df['total_time'] > 60) * 100
print(f"{percentage_over_60_minutes:.2f}% of orders take more than 60 minutes for delivery.")

10.54% of orders take more than 60 minutes for delivery.

10.54% of orders take more than 60 minutes for delivery. Look like huge number of orders taking more than 60 min to delivered from the time the order is placed. To address this issue, businesses should focus on optimizing order processing, streamlining delivery routes, implementing real-time tracking, ensuring adequate staffing and training, leveraging technology, maintaining transparent communication with customers, analyzing delivery data, and emphasizing quality control. Improving delivery times is crucial for enhancing customer satisfaction and operational efficiency.

Question 17: What are your conclusions from the analysis? What recommendations would you like to share to help improve the business? (You can use cuisine type and feedback ratings to drive your business recommendations.) [6 marks]¶

Conclusions:¶

Several conclusions can be drawn about the food delivery service based on above analysis and observations:

  • Popular Choices: Shake Shack is the most popular restaurant, and American cuisine is the preferred choice among customers. This information can help the service tailor its offerings and marketing strategies.*

  • Order Cost Variation: Vietnamese cuisine has the lowest average order cost, indicating it may be a budget-friendly option for customers.*

  • Rating Insights: The presence of a significant number of unrated orders suggests a need for encouraging more customer feedback. Additionally, orders with higher ratings tend to have shorter delivery times and higher costs, while 3-star orders have notably longer preparation times.*

  • Food Preparation Times: Most cuisines require a minimum of 20 minutes for food preparation, with Korean food having relatively shorter delivery times but Vietnamese food taking longer. These insights can aid in better scheduling and preparation management.*

  • Delivery Time Patterns: Weekdays generally experience longer delivery times compared to weekends. This pattern could be due to various factors like traffic or order volume.*

  • Delivery Time Challenges: A concerning finding is that 10.54% of orders take more than 60 minutes for delivery, which may impact customer satisfaction and loyalty.*

  • Weekday vs. Weekend Delivery: On average, weekend deliveries are faster, with a mean delivery time of around 22 minutes, compared to approximately 28 minutes on weekdays.*

In conclusion, these observations provide valuable information for the food delivery service to refine its operations, improve delivery efficiency, gather more customer feedback, and potentially address the issue of orders taking longer than 60 minutes for delivery. Meeting customer expectations and optimizing service quality are essential for success in the competitive food delivery industry.

Recommendations:¶

Based on the observations and conclusions drawn from the data, here are some recommendations for improving the food delivery service:

  • Promote Customer Feedback: Actively encourage customers to leave ratings and reviews for their orders. Consider implementing incentives like loyalty rewards to boost customer engagement and collect valuable insights into their satisfaction levels.*

  • Efficient Order Preparation: Concentrate on reducing the preparation time for 3-star-rated orders, which tend to take longer. Streamline kitchen operations and optimize staff allocation during busy periods to expedite order preparation.*

  • Delivery Time Enhancement: -- Tackle the issue of orders exceeding a 60-minute delivery time. Deploy real-time tracking and monitoring systems to identify and rectify delivery delays. -- Investigate the reasons behind extended delivery times on weekdays and devise strategies to enhance efficiency during these periods, such as optimizing delivery routes and staffing levels.

  • Menu Diversity: While American cuisine is popular, consider expanding the menu to encompass a wider array of choices that cater to diverse customer preferences. Highlight the affordability of Vietnamese cuisine as part of your marketing strategy.*

  • Quality Assurance: Maintain rigorous quality control measures to ensure that all orders consistently meet customer expectations. Consistently delivering high-quality food and service can lead to better ratings and customer loyalty.*

  • Effective Marketing: Leverage the popularity of Shake Shack by prominently featuring it in marketing campaigns. Use customer data for targeted marketing efforts and offer promotions or discounts to drive order volumes.*

  • Weekday Delivery Optimization: Concentrate on strategies to reduce delivery times on weekdays, such as optimizing routes, coordinating with drivers, and implementing technology solutions to enhance efficiency during peak hours.*

  • Data-Driven Decisions: Continue to monitor and analyze delivery data to spot emerging trends and areas for improvement. Regularly update your strategies based on this analysis to maintain competitiveness.*

  • Proactive Customer Communication: Keep customers informed about estimated delivery times and any potential delays. Transparent and proactive communication can boost customer satisfaction, even when there are delays.*

  • Highlight Korean Cuisine: Capitalize on the shorter delivery times for Korean cuisine by promoting it as a quick and convenient option for customers.*

By implementing these recommendations, the food delivery service can enhance its overall performance, elevate customer satisfaction, and remain competitive in the industry. A commitment to continuous improvement and a customer-centric approach will be pivotal for long-term success.
